Business Summary


Manufactures and distributes perfumes and cosmeticsInterparfums engages in designing, manufacturing, and sale of cosmetics and fragrances.It distributes its products through the following brands: Balmain, Boucheron, Jimmy Choo, Karl Lagerfeld, Lanvin, Montblanc, Paul Smith, Repetto, S.T. Dupont, and Van Cleef & Arpels.The company operates through two segments: Perfumes and Fashion.Interparfums was founded by Philippe Bénacin and Jean Madar in 1982 and is headquartered in Paris, France.Number of employees : 257 persons.
 





